From: tonytranrp <100391458+tonytranrp@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Jun 2026 22:56:14 -1000
Subject: [PATCH] clang-mg: add hard compact tests (nested, constexpr)

Two verified hard-scenario tests: a compact struct nested inside another compact struct (outer uses the inner's already-reordered size/align), and a compact struct used in constexpr construction + by-name member reads (constant evaluator follows the reorder consistently). Ground-truth values read from actual layout dumps, not guessed. No compiler change.



diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-constexpr-evaluation.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-constexpr-evaluation.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..52cfacc86
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-constexpr-evaluation.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,23 @@
+// HARD: a compact struct used in constant evaluation. It reorders, yet
+// constexpr construction and by-name member reads still produce the right
+// values -- the constant evaluator follows the reordered decl order
+// consistently, and `.x`/`.n`/`.tag` resolve to the correct members regardless
+// of physical order.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -verify %s
+// expected-no-diagnostics
+
+compact struct Pt { char tag; double x; int n; }; // -> {x, n, tag}, 16 bytes
+static_assert(sizeof(Pt) == 16, "");
+
+constexpr Pt make() {
+  Pt p{};
+  p.x = 1.0;
+  p.n = 7;
+  p.tag = 'z';
+  return p;
+}
+
+static_assert(make().x == 1.0, "");
+static_assert(make().n == 7, "");
+static_assert(make().tag == 'z', "");
diff --git a/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-nested-in-compact.cpp b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-nested-in-compact.cpp
new file mode 100644
index 000000000..004763c48
--- /dev/null
+++ b/clang/test/CXXMG/compact/compact-nested-in-compact.cpp
@@ -0,0 +1,22 @@
+// HARD: a compact struct nested as a field of another compact struct. Each
+// reorders independently, and the outer must place the inner field using the
+// inner's ALREADY-reordered size (16) and alignment (8) -- inner-before-outer
+// completion, no stale size.
+//
+// RUN: %clang_cc1 -std=c++20 -fcxxmg -fsyntax-only -fdump-record-layouts %s | FileCheck %s
+
+compact struct Inner { char c; double d; };           // -> {d, c}, 16 bytes
+compact struct Outer { char a; Inner inner; long l; }; // -> {inner, l, a}, 24 bytes
+
+static_assert(sizeof(Inner) == 16, "inner packs char after double");
+static_assert(sizeof(Outer) == 24, "inner(16)+long(8)+char, padded to 24");
+
+// Inner reorders to {d, c}:
+// CHECK:      struct Inner
+// CHECK-NEXT: double d
+// CHECK-NEXT: char c
+// Outer reorders to {inner, l, a}; the nested inner is itself reordered:
+// CHECK:      struct Outer
+// CHECK-NEXT: struct Inner inner
+// CHECK:      long l
+// CHECK-NEXT: char a
-- 
